body:
@becketqin : Sorry for the delay. The patch looks good overall. 

1. I am wondering if we should do similar things for config changes at the topic level. For example, if someone wants to reduce the retention time of a topic through kafka-config.sh, at the minimum, it will be useful to warn people on the impact of message.timestamp.difference.max.ms.

2. Yes, we could potentially extend validator to do some soft validation. If the validation fails, we just warn instead of fail. This can be done in a separate patch.
